Reinforcement Learning, Probabilistic Methods. 

Reinforcement Learning is the main sub-category of AI that this paper belongs to. The paper introduces a methodology for solving combinatorial optimization problems through the application of reinforcement learning methods. The approach involves analyzing a set of "training" problem instances and learning a search control policy for solving new problem instances. 

Probabilistic Methods are also present in the paper, as the method based on simulated annealing is mentioned as a non-learning search procedure that is less effective than the learned search control policy. Simulated annealing is a probabilistic method for finding a good approximation to the global optimum of a given function.
